cs.CR, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on security guarantees and protection of the Linux kernel.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of the hardware-assisted kernel CFI on the ARM Linux kernel.
- cs.AR (Architecture) is a possible category as the paper utilizes the ARMv8.3 pointer authentication extension for the design.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the deployment of security primitives in the kernel and the differences from their user space application.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper presents a solution for memory protection in the Linux kernel.
